- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a voice-user interaction system based on speech recognition and natural language processing.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper proposes a custom convolutional neural network for search term detection, which is a common technique in computer vision.
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as the paper deals with speech recognition and voice-user interaction.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper proposes a system to help users navigate hospitals, which is a human-computer interaction problem.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a broad category that could also apply as the paper proposes a machine learning model for search term detection.
